race.comment: MARGIN CALL (5)  is a promising type in a top metro stable. Already a two-time winner, including last start when scoring over 1000m at this track. Maps for the softest run and he can go on with the job. CLIMATE CHANGE (7) resumes further improved winning a 66 at Albury. That stacks right up, and with the extra fitness the local is a decent chance to repeat the dose. DESTRUCTIVE DIVA (1) missed a whisker in the same contest, charging home from back in the field. Has a handy 2kg claim and she can feature if the splits come. AEGIPAN (3) keeps winning. This looks tougher, but he has a handy 3kg claim and maps well. Will have plenty of admirers.
